OL,3,CWhy early-morning 'ghost train' will
OL,4,Crun without any passengers
OL,6,FWhat is a 'firebreak' path?
OL,8,FFirebreak paths are planned gaps or
OL,9,Funused time in the train timetable,
OL,10,Fwhich allow services to recover and
OL,11,Fget back on schedule following delays
OL,12,For disruptions. The ORR describes them
OL,13,Fas "relief valves".
